frameDefinitions: The words in this frame describe the manipulation of an Entity by an Agent.
A Figure is characterized as near the Ground, according to some contextually given scale.
The Authorities hold a Suspect under suspicion of having committed a crime (Charges).
A Producer produces a Product from a Resource for commercial purposes. '
A Cognizer has a relatively fixed positive or negative point of view towards an Issue.
An Agent is responsible for having intentionally performed an Act or for being the or a primary instigator behind the Act.
frameExamples: She put her shoes <t>under</t> the table .
The police <t>held</t> Mr. Smith in the slammer on charges of killing his lawyer.
They <t>produced</t> only half of the units after an injunction to follow the environmental policy.
In interviews , it seems like everyone is completely <t>against</t> this expenditure .
It has been determined that a relatively unknown terrorist group is <t>responsible</t> for the recent attacks.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> manipulates an object. <fen>Agent</fen> typically refers to animate beings, but is also extended to mechanical and other inanimate objects.  <fen>Agent</fen> is most frequently expressed as the external argument of verbs:
The <fen>Entity</fen> being manipulated often occurs as the direct object of verbs:

The part of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body being used to manipulate the <fen>Entity</fen> may also be expressed. While the default is for an <fen>Agent</fen> to use his/her hands, other body parts may be specified. This frame element usually occurs as a PP-complement.
When the manipulation takes place
The spatial setting in which the manipulation takes place.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> hold the <fen>Suspect</fen> in custody.
This role identifies the person who is taken into custody and held, under suspicion of having committed a crime.
When the detaining occurs.
Where the detaining takes place.
The person or company that produces the Product.
The <fen>Product</fen> is produced by the <fen>Producer</fen>.
<fen>Factory</fen> identifies the particular plant where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
This Fe identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the product was produced.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Product</fen> is manufactured.
The individual that holds an opinion on an <fen>Issue</fen> or Side.
The matter, usually concerning a course of action, which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has a positive or negative opinion about.
The party or individual (generally associated with a particular position on an <fen>Issue</fen>) that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has an opinion about.
An action taken by a <fen>Side</fen> or a view that the <fen>Side</fen> takes on an issue which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> either supports or opposes.
The time period during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has the indicated point of view towards the <fen>Issue</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> takes <fen>Side</fen>s on an <fen>Issue</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Act</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.

<fex>The cat</fex> is next to the mat.
He was by the park <fex>on Friday</fex>.

Those leather shoes were made <fex>in Italy</fex>.
